# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration Update

## Summary
Updated the Vercel Web Analytics implementation to use the correct Next.js-specific import path.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files

**app/layout.tsx**
- Changed import statement from `@vercel/analytics/react` to `@vercel/analytics/next`
- This is the recommended import path for Next.js projects (both App Router and Pages Router)
- The `<Analytics />` component was already properly placed inside the `<body>` tag after `{children}`

**package-lock.json**
- Updated after running `npm install` to ensure dependencies are properly locked

## Implementation Details

The project already had:
- ✅ @vercel/analytics package installed (version ^1.6.1)
- ✅ Analytics component added to root layout (app/layout.tsx)
- ✅ Component properly placed inside the <body> tag

The only change needed was correcting the import path from `@vercel/analytics/react` to `@vercel/analytics/next`, which is the recommended import for Next.js projects according to Vercel's official documentation.

## Verification

1. ✅ **Build**: Ran `npm run build` - completed successfully
2. ✅ **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` - no new errors introduced (existing errors are pre-existing issues unrelated to this change)
3. ✅ **Tests**: Ran `npm run test` - all 97 tests passed across 7 test files

## Notes

- This is an App Router project (uses `app` directory structure)
- The Analytics component is correctly positioned after the main content in the root layout
- The import path change ensures compatibility with Next.js-specific optimizations
- No additional configuration or environment variables are required for basic analytics tracking
